{
  "texts": [
    "Much of the adversarial literature above is focused on use cases with no human in the loop.",
    "In Church and Yue (2023), we envisioned a human-in-the-loop collaboration of humans with machines.",
    "To make this work, we need to characterize which subtasks are appropriate for humans and which are appropriate for machines.",
    "Evaluations in our field tend to focus on how well the machines are doing by themselves, as opposed to which tasks are appropriate for humans and which are appropriate for machines.",
    "The adversarial literature above is asking the right questions:"
  ]
}